job_description: Company Description: McDonald‚Äôs growth strategy, Accelerating the Arches, encompasses all aspects of our business as the leading global omni-channel restaurant brand. As the consumer landscape shifts we are using our competitive advantages to further strengthen our brand. One of our core growth strategies is to Double Down on the 3Ds (Delivery, Digital and Drive Thru). McDonald‚Äôs will accelerate technology innovation so 65M+ customers a day will experience a fast, easy experience, whether at one of our 25,000 and growing Drive thrus, through McDelivery, dine-in or takeaway. McDonald‚Äôs Global Technology is here to power tomorrow‚Äôs feel-good moments. That‚Äôs why you‚Äôll find us at the forefront of transformative technology, exploring new and innovative ways to serve our millions of customers and spread happiness one delicious Hot Fudge Sundae-dipped fry at a time. Using AI, robotics and emerging tech, we‚Äôre digitizing the Golden Arches. Combine that with our unparalleled global scale, and we‚Äôre reshaping all areas of the business, industry and every community that is home to a McDonald‚Äôs restaurant. We face complex tech challenges every day. But that‚Äôs where our diverse and talented teams come in. They‚Äôre made up of the best and brightest from all over the globe, and they thrive in the space where feel-good meets fast-paced. Check out the McDonald‚Äôs Global Technology Technical Blog to learn how technology and our global team are directly enabling the Accelerating the Arches strategy. Department Overview McDonald‚Äôs, one of the most recognized brands in the world, is seeking a skilled Software Development Engineer to lead the development of our in-store technology as part of Commercial Product & Platform organization. The Commercial Product & Platform vision develops global technology products and platforms that delight our customers and enable our crews to operate our restaurants reliably and effectively. The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing and maintenance of the McDonald‚Äôs restaurant software. Restaurant Technology software includes application user interface, API layer software, data management, and data communication with external systems. The software needs to meet stringent reliability and performance requirements as well as the needs of our customers. The biggest area of increase in our spending has been in technology, which is helping to drive our growth. We‚Äôre looking at how to use technology to improve the customer experience and build new customer experiences. We‚Äôre also exploring technologies that can help us reduce or eliminate repetitive tasks and make employees‚Äô jobs more exciting and rewarding. With all the new projects and initiatives, it is an exciting time to be on the team that is helping to make a Better McDonald's!Accountabilities & Responsibilities Develop marketing automation workflows focused on marketing communications & experience personalization such as push notifications, emails, and mobile app personalized experiences Conceptualize customer segmentation to support Marketing Automation based on knowledge of pre-existing data structures Translate business requests for marketing capabilities, into clear technical requirements that include data properties needed for implementing marketing automations Technical requirement solicitation and documentation skills to effectively capture and communicate marketing automation solutions/initiatives to key collaborators Ensure that all technical work aligns with the business objectives and marketing strategies Triage issues and defects - capturing, prioritizing and remediating for marketing automations Qualifications Basic Qualifications: Bachelor‚Äôs Degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, or similar engineering field or equivalent years of experience. Minimum 1+ years of non-internship professional marketing automation experience with a marketing or advertising automation technology system Experience in implementing marketing automation elements such as segments, audiences, and decision-splits Basic understanding of marketing automation concepts and design principles ‚Äì proven track record to understand how structured data can be translated into marketing segments and other automations that provide personalized experiences/communications to customers Understanding of core technologies for web content development- HTML, CSS, and JavaScript Extensive experience in working with key data interchange formats including JSON and XML, demonstrating a strong ability to integrate, manipulate, and manage complex data structures across diverse systems and applications Ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams in sophisticated environments Excellent documentation and communication skills to bridge the gap between business strategy and technical teams. Hands on experience with JIRA/Confluence expected Preferred Skills: Front-end development skills specific to marketing automation. Proficiency in templating languages such as Liquid, Jinja, Handlebars or similar language Knowledge of working with key data interchange formats including JSON and XML, demonstrating a strong ability to integrate, manipulate, and manage complex data structures across diverse systems and applications Compensation Bonus Eligible: Yes Benefits Eligible: YesSalary Range The expected salary range for this role is $84,051.00 - $105,064.00 per year The above represents the expected salary range for this job requisition. Ultimately, in determining your pay, we may also consider your experience, and other job-related factors. Additional Information: Benefits eligible: This position offers health and welfare benefits, a 401(k) plan, adoption assistance program, educational assistance program, flexible ways of working, and time off policies (including sick leave, parental leave, and vacation/PTO). Eligibility requirements apply to some benefits and may depend on job classification and length of employment. Bonus eligible: This position is eligible for a bonus, calculated based on individual and company performance. McDonald‚Äôs is an equal opportunity employer committed to the diversity of our workforce. We promote an inclusive work environment that creates feel-good moments for everyone. McDonald‚Äôs provides reasonable accommodations to qualified individuals with disabilities as part of the application or hiring process or to perform the essential functions of their job. If you need assistance accessing or reading this job posting or otherwise feel you need an accommodation during the application or hiring process, please contact mcdhrbenefits@us.mcd.com. Reasonable accommodations will be determined on a case-by-case basis. This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training. Nothing in this job posting or description should be construed as an offer or guarantee of employment.

The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the world‚Äôs leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, we‚Äôre focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, and‚Äîabove all‚Äìdriving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zip‚Äôs core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, we‚Äôre committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. üìà Start-up equity ü¶∑ Full health, vision & dental coverage üçΩÔ∏è Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees üöç Commuter benefit üö† Team building events & happy hours üå¥ Flexible PTO üíª Apple equipment plus home office budget üí∏ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We encourage all candidates to apply even if your experience doesn't exactly match up to our job description. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

DescriptionSummary: The Technology Delivery Analyst is responsible is responsible for delivering technical value and solutions as an engineer, developer advocate, systems analyst, test automation, or other technology role after their initial completion of the Elevate Program.Duties and Responsibilities: Work alongside an experienced member of the team to gain a better understanding of their role.Work collaboratively with technical teams interfacing with assigned application or platform.Create and maintain system documentation, manuals, policy documents, etc.Research and analyze production support issues.Participates in production releases as scheduled.Software Engineer Duties and Responsibilities:Participate in the analysis and review of epics, features, and user stories.Participate in Agile ceremonies such as Daily Stand Ups, Sprint Planning, Sprint Demos/Reviews, Sprint Retrospectives, and Backlog Refinement.Participate in the creation, development, testing and implementation of software solutions.Database Engineer Duties and Responsibilities:Participate in the creation, development, implementation, configuration, maintenance, and support of data models for databases, data marts, and data warehouses.Aid in developing methods to store, organize, and report data while incorporating development operations automation where appropriate.Proactively investigate and troubleshoot technical challenges, and aid in corrective action.Test Automation Analyst Duties and Responsibilities:Analyze and translate functional requirements to create and execute test cases for large business initiatives. Automate and execute these test cases on regular basis.Write, review, and maintain the automation test scripts in test automation tools.Perform all aspects of verification, including integration testing, functional testing, and regression testing.Perform other duties and projects as assigned.Basic Qualifications: Bachelor‚Äôs Degree0 to 2 years of experience in an engineer, developer, test automation, or systems analysis role or transferrable skills through coursework, internships, or work experience in lieu of participation in the Elevate Program.Preferred Qualifications: Basic understanding of Waterfall or Agile delivery through coursework, internships, or work experience.Technical writing capabilities with strong attention to detail.Business and Technology aptitude with the ability to learn the processes, procedures, technologies, and platforms associated with their role.Ability to communicate effectively and confidently with team members and colleagues.Highly motivated with good organizational, analytical, decision making, and problem-solving skills.Strong written and verbal communication and active listening skills.Ability to create and deliver presentations.Ability to build credibility and strong partnerships while working collaboratively within their team and segment.Ability to effectively handle multiple tasks and execute in a high-pressure environment.Ability to address conflict professionally and respectfully.Exempt Status: (Yes = not eligible for overtime pay) (No = eligible for overtime pay)YesWorkplace Type:OfficeOur Approach to Office Workplace TypeCertain positions outside our branch network may be eligible for a flexible work arrangement. We‚Äôre combining the best of both worlds: in-office and work from home. Our approach enables our teams to deepen connections, maintain a strong community, and do their best work. Remote roles will also have the opportunity to come together in our offices for moments that matter. Specific work arrangements will be provided by the hiring team.Huntington will not sponsor applicants for this position for immigration benefits, including but not limited to assisting with obtaining work permission for F-1 students, H-1B professionals, O-1 workers, TN workers, E-3 workers, among other immigration statuses. Overview

 

Reporting to the Associate Director, Gift Records, the Data Management Support II provides support to the Office of Alumni and Donor Records in receiving, recording and legally acknowledging charitable contributions to the University. 

 

Princeton University Advancement works to inform, inspire, and involve Princeton‚Äôs global community of alumni, parents, and friends in ways that enable the University to fulfill its mission of advancing learning through scholarship, research, and teaching to serve humanity.

Responsibilities

Gift Processing

  • Enters new gifts, pledges, matching gifts, trust income, ORPA, payroll deductions, and pledge payments of all types including cash, credit cards, securities, and gifts-in-kind from all sources.\
  • Runs standard gift and pledge reports for gift processing.
  • Reconciles daily transactions against multiple reports.
  • Participates in daily gift processing rotations for error trapping, balancing, on-line credit card processing, acknowledgment production and deposits to the Cashier.
  • Verifies gift acknowledgment letters for donors.
  • Requests new donor records and changes to existing records.
  • Serves as back up to Data Management Support III in receiving mail, opening, sorting, researching donor information and coding unrestricted and Friends gifts.

Special Projects:

  • Assists in the entry preparation for Gifts to Princeton.
  • Participates in Alumni Records and Gift Records cross training initiatives.
  • Other related tasks as assigned.

Qualifications

  • High School diploma required.
  • Knowledge of or ability to quickly learn OnBase Document Imaging system for document retrieval.
  • Strong knowledge and use of Excel for basic spreadsheets.
  • Strong knowledge and use of Access for Gifts to Princeton entries.
  • Strong knowledge and use of Stripes to enter gifts, generate standard reports, perform inquiries and verify information.
  • Good oral and written communication skills to respond to inquiries.
  • Good organization skills.
  • Accuracy, close attention to detail, a change-friendly attitude, strong work ethic and discretion in dealing with confidential information.
  • Commitment to University Advancement‚Äôs mission to inform, involve, and inspire Princeton‚Äôs global community of alumni and friends, and adhering to its guiding principles of High Performance, Innovation, Civility, and Collaboration.
  • Demonstrated ability to work effectively and build relationships with individuals from diverse backgrounds, identities, abilities, and experiences.

Preferred Qualifications

  • Strong knowledge and spectrum of gift recording activities, policies and procedures.
  • Knowledge of Princeton‚Äôs mission
  • Experience in higher education
